
tools for group server mangement in the AWS autoscale system
any command will automatically retrieve required addresses for role

ssh to the admin server (current ec2-user@107.23.159.233) and cd tools/fabric/


* any_sudo 
	DESC: run any command with root privileges
	USAGE:
		cd any_sudo
		export FAB_CMD='command*'; fab fabric_command** 
		*  -- shell command for remote execution with sudo
		** -- fab coomand. list commands with "fab help" 
	EXAMPLE:
	        reboot all web_server instances:

		export FAB_CMD='reboot' ; fab web_server 


* restart_services
	DESC: hard restart koding processes (kill -9)
	USAGE:
		cd restart_services
		fab fabric_command** 
		** -- fab coomand. list commands with "fab help" 
	EXAMPLE:
	        restart processes on the web_server nodes:
		fab restart_web_server
		
		restart processes on web servers and social worker servers:
		fab restart_web_server restart_socialworker


* speedup_deploy
	DESC: kick chef-client to deploy updates
	USAGE:
		cd speedup_deploy
		fab fabric_command** 
		** -- fab coomand. list commands with "fab help" 
	EXAMPLE:
	        speedup deployment processes on the web_server nodes:
		fab speedup_deploy_on_web_server
		
		speedup deployment processes on web servers and social worker servers:
		fab speedup_deploy_on_web_server speedup_deploy_on_socialworker



* update_os
	DESC: update OS packages
	USAGE:
		cd update_os
		fab fabric_command** 
		** -- fab coomand. list commands with "fab help" 
	EXAMPLE:
	        update packages on the web_server nodes:
		fab update_os_on_web_server
		
		speedup deployment processes on web servers and social worker servers:
		fab update_os_on_web_server update_os_on_socialworker

